Snow and ice: 24 departments in alarm level orange 
The snow episodes still involve traffic difficulties, in particular in the secondary traffic networks of Brittany and tend to influence different economic activities. 
There are twenty-four departments now due to the threatening snow and ice risk in alarm level orange. 
The regions yours, Eure-et-Loir, Deux-Sèvres and Vienne are the already in alarm level orange contained 20 departments added; 18 since Wednesday afternoon and two, the Dordogne and the Gironde, then later in the night. 
According to Météo France, the intense snow showers affect the north of the Gironde as well as the Charentes, it snows easily on the et Ile-de-France. 
In the affected departments snow coverages are expected of 2 to 5 cm occasionally also of 7 to 10 cm, as well as 1 to 3 cm, even up to 5 cm in the Paris region. 
The regions Charente, Charente-maritime, Côtes d'Armor, Finistère, Gironde, Dordogne, Poitou and the regions Basse-Normandie, Ile-de-France and Limousin, are affected. 
The snowfalls are considerable enough in order to cause traffic hindrances and to influence certain economic activities, predicts Météo France. 
In the region Côtes d'Armor several regional streets are spaced for the heavy traffic from more than 7,5 tons, under that the traffic axes Guingamp-Lannion and Saint-Brieuc-Loudéac. 
The call progress state of the secondary traffic networks in Brittany is very difficult according to the traffic policemen that warn against using the own vehicle only in the emergency, and the use of some TER coaches became the entire day over deleted. 
In the Picardie the school traffic was canceled for Thursday. 
For the heavy traffic no specific restricting measures were planned at the Wednesday evening. 
The prefecture "calls the motorists for highest caution on the streets as well as for the corresponding adaptation of their driving behavior." 
The general management for Civilian aviation (DGAC) asked the airlines to delete to Roissy and to 10% of the flights starting from Orly due to the expected, strong snowfalls % of theirs from the Paris airport on Thursday 25. 
The DGAB recommends the flight passengers to contact their airline. 
